cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MS, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with medical image segmentation. The use of shape priors and mesh representation also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The optimization problem formulation and solution using Markov random fields and graph cuts suggest that it could also belong to the mathematical software (cs.MS) sub-category. Finally, the use of gradient vector flows and the potential for extension to multiple interacting objects suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
